{
  "stem": "1765.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 117.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And I still watch on television and remember going in Vilna with my father who came from the dead, just like the father in the movie.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then, of course, second World War was becoming more and more of a reality in Vilna.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Even though we didn't have a German occupation, we had a lot of people from Warsaw and Lodz and central Poland who were running east.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And everyone took in refugees into their homes.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we had people coming and going, sleeping on the sofa in the dining room and in the study.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not that I know of.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't say they didn't, I just don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I'm very careful about making such statements because if I don't know, maybe they did.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And now we will come to-- to this enormous change in our lives, but I must say that having been sent to Siberia was a blessing in disguise for us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In 1941, the three Baltic countries-- Lithuania, Latvia, and Estonia-- where annexed by the Soviet Union.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Businesses were [PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] taken away from their owners.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The Soviets ruled the three Baltic countries.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "The Russian soldiers came in.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Russian administrators came in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in June, 1939-- it began earlier, actually, but I didn't know about it-- Soviet government soldiers came into homes of so-called enemies of the people-- capitalists and enemies of the people-- and arrested us with bayonets held over our heads.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Everyone sat with a soldier standing over us.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "My father was called by an uncle to see what was happening in-- in their father's house across the landing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And he went there, and he didn't come back until the soldiers pushed him, in his pajamas, into our apartment.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
